Paper: hep-th/0211165

Date: 2002-11-18

Title: Newton's Second Law in a Noncommutative Space

Authors: Juan M. Romero, J.A. Santiago and J. David Vergara

Comments: 7 pages, References added

In this work we show that corrections to the Newton's second law appears ifwe assume that the phase space has a symplectic structure consistent with therules of commutation of noncommutative quantum mechanis. In the central fieldcase we find that the correction term breaks the rotational symmetry. Inparticular, for the Kepler problem, this term takes the form of a Coriolisforce produced by the weak gravitational field far from a rotating massiveobject.